dct_title_s: Civitavecchia / compiled and drawn by C.I.U., Feb. 1943
dct_description_sm: Relief shown by contours and rock drawings. "Compiled and drawn by C.I.U., Feb. 1943. Photolithographed at the War Office, 1943." "9-43." Military grid (blue). "Grid provisional." Important buildings are named. "Published by War Office, 1943." Reprinted 1943 by A.M.S. This is a map of the city of Civitavecchia, Italy, shown at a 1:10,000 scale. The map was created for use by War and Navy Department agencies during World War II.
dct_creator_sm: Great Britain. Royal Air Force. Central Interpretation Unit
dct_publisher_sm: [London] : War Office. General Staff. Geographical Section, 1943.
Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, U.S. Army, 1943.
